  "body": "#### System information\r\nI have setup polygon archive node with Erigon + Heimdall setup and my Erigon is stuck at processing block header (40449538) for more than 2 days with following log errors:\r\n```\r\nMar 19 22:34:18 polygon-archive-2 erigon[117523]: [INFO] [03-19|22:34:18.804] [2/16 Headers] No block headers to write in this log period block number=40449538\r\nMar 19 22:34:18 polygon-archive-2 erigon[117523]: [INFO] [03-19|22:34:18.804] Req/resp stats                           req=98 reqMin=40446917 reqMax=40447206 skel=17 skelMin=40449538 skelMax=40744450 resp=130 respMin=40446919 respMax=40541200 dups=1021\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, Heimdall is completely synced and working fine. Also, I have verified Heimdall Rest Server is working fine.\r\n\r\nErigon version: erigon version 2.35.2-stable-800645ee\r\nHeimdall version: 0.3.0\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\nErigon Commit hash: 800645eee\r\n\r\nErigon Command (with flags/config):\r\n```\r\nerigon --chain=bor-mainnet  --snapshots=true --bor.heimdall=http://localhost:1317 --http --http.addr=0.0.0.0 --http.port=8545 --http.compression --http.vhosts=* --http.corsdomain=* --http.api=eth,debug,net,trace,web3,erigon,bor --ws --ws.compression --rpc.gascap=300000000 --metrics --metrics.addr=0.0.0.0 --metrics.port=6969\r\n```\r\n\r\nChain/Network:  137 mainnet\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nErigon should start syncing the later blocks\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nErigon is stuck at processing block header.\r\n\r\n",
